wiki.text:
'TPH' may refer to: *Walther TPH, a semi-automatic pistol made by the German
arms manufacturer Walther. *'Trains Per Hour' (UK), an abbreviation used to
indicate train service/schedules for a particular railway station. *Tryptophan
hydroxylase, an enzyme. *'Tonnes Per Hour', an abbreviation used to specify the
capacity of industrial machinery such as boiler, conveyor belt and vibrating
feeder. *Total Petroleum Hydrocarbon, an expression of chemical content.
